to England. I‚Äôve studied with all of the masters of Egypt. Yes, I really
deserve to be seen as a healer and a teacher.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>But I learned, through humility, to remember the simplicity that, of
myself, I can do nothing. I cultivated within myself the art of always
being a <em>student of Love</em>, and not the <em>professor</em> of Love, who thinks he‚Äôs
done just because he has a lot of letters after his name. So you see
that as you progress, and as you allow more of the abundance of God‚Äôs
Love to flow through you, you see you begin to stand up out of the
